description: Rya is a Gideon and a resident of the world called Terrenos. She is one of the first to discover Michael upon his arrival and flies him to Rook. Rook decides to make Rya Michael's protector, for he is destined to defeat the evil overlord, God King Lore.
name: Rya

description: Ansari is a gideon from the world of Terrenos. He is one of the three (along with Rya and Shavo) to discover Michael when he first arrives in Terrenos.
name: Ansari

description:
Officer Brooks is the lead investigator to the disappearance of Michael. He contacts the family once a barbarian looking man claiming to be Michael is brought into the precinct.

Aaron (Michael's father) makes a snide comment to his estranged wife Wendy about Officer Brooks being her boyfriend.
name: Officer Brooks

description:
Brennan Rhodes is the older brother of Michael. On his brother's birthday, Brennan and his mom were decorating the house for the party while his father played catch with Michael, just outside the woods. Michael chases after the ball into the woods and is never seen again.

One year later a mysterious, barbarian looking man is found wandering the woods who claims to be Michael. Brennan enters the interrogation room to try and discern one way or another if this was truely his brother. Aaron (their father) recognizes the man as his lost son and helps free him the interrogation room. Brennan leads Barbarian to where his weapons are stored.

Michael claims that he spent years in a land called Terrenos, defeated the evil overlord "God King Lore" and returned to earth chasing residence of Terrenos and agents of God King Lore. Michael's must defeat these agents before they destroy the earth.
name: Brennan Rhodes

description:
Wendy Rhodes is the mother of Brennan and Michael, wife to Aaron (although she has filed for divorce). Her marriage became estranged when Michael disappeared into the woods while playing catch with his father, on his birthday.

One year later a mysterious, barbarian looking man is found wandering the woods who claims to be Michael.
name: Wendy Rhodes

description:
Aaron Rhodes is the father of Brennan and Michael, husband to Wendy (although she has filed for divorce). His marriage became estranged when Michael disappeared into the woods while Aaron plaid catch with him on his birthday.

Aaron is accused of murdering his son, although never arrested.

One year later a mysterious, barbarian looking man is found wandering the woods who claims to be Michael and Aaron. Upon seeing this older version of his son, Aaron recognizes him and helps free him the interrogation room.
name: Aaron Rhodes

description:
On Michael's birthday, while Brennan and his mom were decorating the house for his party, he plays catch with his father just outside the woods. Michael chases after the ball into the woods and is transported to Terrenos.

One year later he returns to earth older and is found wandering the woods and taken to the police station for interrogation.

Brennan enters the interrogation room to try and discern one way or another if this was truly his brother. Aaron (their father) recognizes him as his lost son and helps free him the interrogation room. Brennan leads him to where his weapons are stored.

Michael spent years in a land called Terrenos, defeated the evil overlord "God King Lore" and returned to earth chasing residence of Terrenos and agents of God King Lore. Michael's must defeat these agents before they destroy the earth.

The story cuts between present day on Earth and his adventures in Terrenos. Upon arriving at Terrenos he is discovered by Gideons called Ansari, Shavo and Rya. They take him to meet Rook who reveals that Michael is destined to be Terrenos's champion and free it's people from God King Lore's control.

In a twist, it is revealed that Michael is actually possessed by God King Lore and a has returned to Earth a his agent.
name: Michael Rhodes

description:
Rook is a resident of the magical land called Terrenos. He is allied with the Gideons (winged children) and is attempting to overthrow God King Lore. He has Michael Rhodes brought to him as soon as he is found in Terrenos and serves as his trainer and guide.

Rook explains to Michael that he is destined to be the champion who will defeat God King Lore and free the citizens from slavery.
name: Rook

deck: A classic mad scientist of the Victorian era, he has built a machine that can control electric fields.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Dr. Pretorius works for Mr. Peebles and the Hand of Four, a secret group of plutocrats who want to take over Victorian Britain. He builds a machine that can control electric fields in a number of incredible ways, including the creation of lighting bolts capable of assassinating people on the street on a cloudless day, the creation of a stasis field powerful enough to trap Bozz, an alien capable of manipulating energy in a variety of ways himself, and even the resurrection of the dead!

When Mandy Flynn, Salem Hawkshaw, and Bozz find out about the machine and the Hand of Four, they drop in on his secret laboratory. Pretorius manages to trap Bozz, but the others break him free and Bozz overloads the machine. It explodes, killing the doctor.
name: Dr. Pretorius

deck: Leader of the Hand of Four, a group of plutocrats working behind the scenes in Victorian England.
description:
Story Arcs

Mr. Peebles is a member of the Hand of Four, a group of self-interested rich businessman who want to take over Britain during the Victorian era.

They engage Lord Giles Morgan to manipulate Parliament for them, and pay Dr. Pretorius to create a wonder-working machine that can control electric fields. They use this machine to resurrect Morgan twice after unfortunate deaths.

However the detectives Mandy Flynn, Salem Hawkshaw, and Bozz find out about their plans and try to stop them. The Hand manages to temporarily entrap Bozz but the others rescue him. The machine explodes and kills Morgan and Pretorius, but Peebles's fate is unclear. Presumably he was arrested afterwards.
name: Mr. Peebles

deck: A scheming Victorian British Lord who has mysteriously survived death, twice!
description:
Major Story Arcs

Giles Morgan is a British Lord in the Victorian era. He makes a deal with a secret group of plutocrats known as the Hand of Four, led by Mr. Peebles. They have created a machine with the help of Dr. Pretorius that can control electrical fields and plan to use it, and the political influence of Lord Morgan, to take over the country. Their deal is that they will use the machine's ability to resurrect the dead in exchange for Lord Morgan manipulating the government on their behalf. In fact, they have already resurrected him twice!

One of Morgan's secretaries gets a hint of what's going on and hires the detective team of Flynn and Bosworth to investigate. However Giles uses the machine to kill her with a man-made bolt of lightning before she can give out all his secrets.

The detectives look into the case anyway and find out about Giles's involvement. He stonewalls them, but they eventually find the machine. During the pitched battle, the machine overloads and Giles and Pretorius are killed.
name: Lord Giles Morgan

deck: Inspector Fitzroy is an upper-crust Victorian Londoner who also works for Scotland Yard.  He is attracted to detective Mandy Flynn.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Inspector Fitzroy first catches wind of the unusual talents and interests of the detective team of Boswell and Flynn after they stop Lord Giles, Dr. Pretorius, and the Hand of Four.

Raising Hell

Based on this success, he hires them to investigate a series of demonic appearances. After meeting them, he also starts to become romantically interested in the bodacious Mandy Flynn, occasionally asking her out to very posh restaurants (which his family owns), although his plans are usually blocked by his romantic rival, Salem Hawkshaw. Hawkshaw is a rootin'-tootin' cowboy of the American west, and takes issues with Fitzroy's airs. Fitzroy is a member of the highest society who happens to be slumming as an inspector because he thinks it is important work. Although he is very conservative himself, he appreciates the work Mandy and Bozz do on their outre subjects, and once again they solve the case, tracing the demons back to a secret sorcerer, Harrison Townes.

The Tomorrow Man

Fitzroy discovers that a number of murder victims have strange objects upon their person--objects that we would recognize as a digital watch, velcro, and so on, but which do not exist in his era. He once again calls on Mandy and Bozz to look into the matter, while once again trying to put the moves on Mandy. The detectives once again solve the case: the objects come from a time machine invented by the mad scientist Dr. Paine, who is killed in the confrontation.

The Cobblestone Jungle

Fitzroy is later contacted by Chief Baka, an Oxford-educated African leader. A sacred jewel was stolen from his tribe, and he suspects it was smuggled into England. Fitzroy once again asks Mandy and Bozz to look into it, and he finally manages to avoid Salem and take Mandy on a date at an exclusive restaurant. Mandy reciprocates his interest and apparently stays the night at his place.

She, Bozz, and Salem once again solve the case and find the jewel, which had been stolen by the explorer Colonel Carruthers. When they return it to Chief Baka, the reserved Fitzroy is stunned to see the equally-cultured Baka fall down and worship Bozz. It seems that Baka's people have a legend about Bozz's race of aliens, which they believe to be gods.

King Solomon's Spaceship

As an agent of the Crown, Fitzroy accompanies Mandy, Salem, Bozz, and Baka back to Baka's homeland. where Bozz hopes to find other traces of his kind. The friction between Fitzroy and Salem heats up as they both compete over Mandy, but they both start to annoy her with their childishness; and in any case she is in love with Bozz. Finally after they escape a veldt fire by jumping into a mud pool, their tempers flare and they get into a fist fight.

Fitzroy, who was trained in pugilism as a student, gives as good as he gets against the ex-boxer Salem. They start to have grudging respect for each other due to their equality as fighters. Ultimately they realize that Mandy might be in danger from a shifty man they met earlier, Jan Kruger, and they rush off to save her together.

They save her as a team. After Kruger is defeated, they return home to London as friends, although all of their mutual romantic entanglements remain unresolved.
name: Colin Fitzroy

deck: A well-to-do Victorian who is also a failed amateur wizard.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Bradley Townes is from a rich Victorian England family, and is bored with his place in life. His brother Harrison works as an antiques dealer, and has been disinherited due to the fact that he actually wanted a job, instead of just living in the lap of luxury. Bradley, however, remains the family favorite, and unknown to him, Harrison is determined to get revenge on him.

Harry has a magic orb, and is secretly a fairly skilled wizard. He gets Bradley interested in the dark arts and gives him an orb as well, but sabotages it so that all the spells cast through it are warped failures.

Bradley accidentally disfigures himself and turns his head upside-down! Fearful of discovery, he becomes a recluse even from his wife Samantha. However, in his attempts to fix himself, he keeps summoning demons to London and causing havoc. The detectives Mandy Flynn, Salem Hawkshaw, and Bozz stumble upon the case and begin investigating. Harry summons some demons of his own to attack them but they fend them off.

The detectives eventually find out about Bradley, who is distraught at his situation. When Samantha sees him, she faints. The detectives confront Harrison and stop him.

Harry destroys his own orb out of anger and kills himself, leaving Bradley in his deformed state. It is unknown how Samantha deals with Bradley's deception and disfigurement.
name: Bradley Townes

deck: Antiques dealer and secret wizard bent on revenge against his brother.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Harrison Townes is from a rich Victorian England family. He works as an antiques dealer, and has been disinherited due to the fact that he actually wanted a job, instead of just living in the lap of luxury. His brother Bradley, however, remains the family favorite, and Harrison is determined to get revenge on him.

Harry has a magic orb, and is secretly a fairly skilled wizard. He gets Bradley interested in the dark arts and gives him an orb as well, but sabotages it so that all the spells cast through it are warped failures.

Bradley accidentally disfigures himself and turns his head upside-down. Fearful of discovery, he becomes a recluse even from his wife Samantha. However, in his attempts to fix himself, he keeps summoning demons to London and causing havoc. The detectives Mandy Flynn, Salem Hawkshaw, and Bozz stumble upon the case and begin investigating. Harry summons some demons of his own to attack them but they fend them off.

The detectives eventually find out about Bradley and confront Harrison (who has been pretending to help Bradley). Harry fights back and summons a huge demon horde, but Bozz uses his unique alien abilities to stop them.

Harry destroys his own orb out of anger and kills himself, leaving Bradley in his deformed state.
name: Harrison Townes

deck: Worried wife of Bradley Townes, a amateur sorcerer.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Samantha Townes is a well-to-do woman in Victorian England. Her husband Bradley, who is the scion of a rich family, has been acting strangely, having ensconced himself in his room for days, allowing no one to see him.

The detectives Mandy Flynn, Salem Hawkshaw, and Bozz stop by seeking the source of some mysterious demonic activity, which they have traced to her home.

She lets them in and tells them the story about her husband, as well as about his brother Harrison, an antiques dealer who had been disinherited due to the fact that he actually wanted a job, instead of just living in the lap of luxury. The brothers had not been getting along but recently they had gotten back together.

The detectives question Harry in his shop of unusual and occult items, but he sends them off. After a run-in with some demons the detectives come back and insist on seeing Bradley. It turns out that he has been trying to learn magic from Harry, but his spells have all been going wrong, and he turned his head upside-down!

Harry shows up and they confront each other. Harry has actually purposefully been sabotaging Bradley's spells out of frustration at his family. Samantha faints at seeing her disfigured husband.

Harry escapes and the detectives eventually stop him, but Bradley is stuck the way he is. It us unknown whether Samantha is able to accept him in his new form.
name: Samantha Townes

deck: A mad scientist who builds a Time Shooter that keeps bringing anachronistic objects from the future back into Victorian times.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Dr. Paine is a utopian with governmental ideals still held by some a century later (and less topical when he was written in the mid-1980s): he wants to live without government interference in his life and work.

Paine lives in a giant secret hideout in the Victorian London sewers, which he has managed to transform in to a mise-en-scene similar to a Georgian villa, populated by his many similarly-utopian followers wearing Roman togas and acting like hippies a la the Summer of Love.

He builds a "self-locomoting, steam-driven, temporal transfer machine" or "time shooter": basically a tank with a time gun. He hopes to use it to send Parliament to the future so his time will no longer have to deal with government. Whatever the gun hits is sent to the future, and something similar from the future comes back in its place. However the machine doesn't fully work yet and keeps killing the people being sent to Paine's time, so he dumps their bodies (and their various anachronistic objects like digital watches and velcro) in the river.

This eventually catches the attention of Scotland Yard, and Inspector Fitzroy enlists Amanda Flynn, Bozz, and Salem Hawkshaw in the case, knowing their interest in unusual phenomena.

Bozz ends up being brought to Paine's hideout by a group of orphans to heal his temporary blindness. Paine hopes to gain Bozz as an ally, but Bozz rejects him and when the other detectives arrive they defeat Paine and his machine. It gets plugged up and explodes, killing Paine.
name: Doctor Alfred Paine

deck: A homeless orphan in Victorian London, he helps out the detective team of Boswell & Flynn.
description:
Major Story Arcs

The Tomorrow Man

Ollie, a streetwise orphan in the mode of Oliver Twist, first meets the alien Bozz as Ollie tries to pickpocket a gentleman at the carnival. Bozz stops the man from beating Ollie, and Ollie decides to take advantage of Bozz instead. He gets Bozz to steal the man's wallet back using his alien powers. Realizing that Bozz's naivete makes his easy to manipulate, he brings him back to his gang of orphans. After some more thefts, however, Bozz's good nature begins to rub off on him. So when a press gang tries to kidnap Bozz and accidentally blinds him, Ollie and his friends decide to help him.

They bring him to a mysterious doctor who has a secret hideout in the sewers. The doctor takes Bozz in but kicks out Ollie and his friends, so Ollie tells Bozz's partners Mandy Flynn and Salem Hawkshaw, where he is.

The three of them rescue Bozz from the doctor, who is actually a mad scientist who created a time machine. Ollie himself destroys the time machine and Mandy gives him a reward, thus starting his new relationship as an assistant to their detective business.

The Cobblestone Jungle

When Mandy and Bozz are hired to find an African jewel that was smuggled into the country, Ollie finds out which ship it arrived on, and helps them meet the captain.
name: Ollie

deck: Estranged and deadbeat father of detective Mandy Flynn.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Thorpe leaves his family before his daughter Mandy Flynn was born. She grows up without hearing from him in 20 years, but when she becomes known as a detective, he contacts her.

Conflicted, she rides out to the country to talk to him at his tavern. He tells her that there has been a series of gruesome and mysterious murders in the last few weeks, which has led to a lack of sales at the bar, as people hide out at home.

Furious that he contacted her solely over monetary concerns, she leaves in a huff, but continues to investigate the situation with her friends Salem and Bozz anyway. They determine that a series of paintings with occult themes, made by the local Squire Blakblud, have been coming to life at night an terrorizing the area.

They confront him just as his final painting, of Satan himself, is about to come to life. He had made a deal with Hell to let them take over the world, as long as they provided prosperity to their own small village. Nobody else seems to think this is a great idea, but Egan likes it because it means more sales at his pub. He runs off with the painting in an attempt to save it and release Satan, but the detectives manage to get the painting back. Mandy destroys it using Satan's own hellfire, and punches out her dad for being such a loathsome jerk.
name: Egan Thorpe

deck: A desperate but misguided Victorian country squire who makes a bad art deal with Satan.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Squire Blakblud lives in a small village in Victorian England. He feels responsible for its fortunes, but it has fallen upon hard times. In an effort to save the village, he makes a deal with Satan: he'll make a number of paintings of various demons so they can come alive and take over the world, and in exchange Satan will make his village prosperous again.

While this deal may seem like a poor idea to some, Blakblud takes it and starts making painting using magical paint. He has the villagers put them up all over town, although they are not surprisingly reluctant to do so.

However, intrepid detective Mandy Flynn and her friends Salem and Bozz happen to come to town right at that point to meet with Mandy's estranged father. They find out that demons have been terrorizing the area and investigate.

While Mandy is rather taken with Blakblud's looks and money, they soon realize he is the source of the problems. They stay at his house over night, posing as art journlists, but he makes his final painting, of Satan himself, and escapes to the town church through a secret passage.

They chase after him in time to see the painting start to come alive, at which the Squire finally seems to realize he may have made a mistake. Mandy luckily manages to destroy it using Satan's own hellfire, and the village and world are saved. It is unclear whether the squire's role in all this becomes public knowledge.
name: Squire Blakblud

deck: Chief of an unnamed African village that is home to a large diamond mine and worships aliens.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Baka is highly educated, first by missionaries and then in universities abroad, including Oxford. He normally wears business suits but puts on his ceremonial garb on on special occasions.

His country has some diamond deposits that England has been mining, but one of their sacred jewels was stolen and taken to England. The British agree to help find it so they are not blamed for its theft.

Inspector Fitzroy of Scotland Yard takes on the case and asks the detectives Mandy Flynn, Salem Hawkshaw, and the alien Bozz to help. They find the jewel and return it to Baka.

However, when Baka sees Bozz for the first time, he is stunned and starts to worship him: the legends of his people speak of people that look like Bozz as gods. Furthermore, Bozz recognizes the crystal as being one of his race's power sources. He realizes that they may have left some other trace in the area that might help him get back to his home planet.

Baka therefore leads them all back to his village in search of more alien evidence. There, he is a beloved leader. They find another European, Jan Kruger, also staying at the village. He is searching for a tunnel to the center of the earth but decides Bozz would be an even better attraction and decides to capture him.

They all continue on to the source of the crystal together, and have various difficulties dealing with wild rivers and veldt fires, which Baka helps them safely through.

They split up and Bozz and Mandy find a spaceship, but it is destroyed along with Kruger. Baka finds them soon after, and the detectives return home.
name: Chief Baka

deck: Adventurer who seeks revenge on the government of Victorian England with a laser cannon.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Carruthers was once a respected British explorer of Africa. However he accidentally claimed some territory that was rightfully due to another, and there was a scandal. He lost all his honor and privileges.

Seeking revenge, he stole a jewel from a local African tribe, led by Chief Baka, and used it to power a laser cannon. He brought it to England to destroy the Tower of London.

Uncomfortable in England, he actually rebuilds the inside of his house to look like a jungle and employed many Africans as aides.

However, the detectives Mandy Flynn, Salem Hawkshaw, and the alien Bozz find out and come to his house. He captures them and sets his men upon them, but Bozz defeats them with his superhuman strength.

In the meantime, the Colonel escapes in a hydrogen balloon, with the laser cannon in the basket. Bozz flies up to stop him. After dodging several attacks, he plugs his pistol with his finger. Carruthers fires anyway, destroying the gun, and partially blinding himself. He then starts taking shots with the laser, but hits and explodes the balloon, killing himself. Bozz, however, survives.
name: Colonel Alexander Carruthers

deck: Explorer and opportunist.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Kruger is searching Africa for the legendary center of the earth, called Agharta, so that he can exploit it for tourism and gold. Previously he was a slaver and a rhinoceros horn poacher.

He happens upon Chief Baka's village and there meets Bozz, an alien, and realizes that he could be worth even more money. He hides his true motives and comes along with the others to seek the place where, according to the tribe's legends, the "gods" (or aliens) first came to Earth--a place Bozz seeks so he can hopefully return home.

He tries to capture Bozz one night with a net, but Bozz easily rips it off and tells the local baboons to attack Kruger and his men. They run off, screaming.

He survives, however, and sets a fire to get rid of the Bozz and his friends, to no avail. He finally catches Bozz by threatening Mandy, his friend. However that night they are rescued by their other friends Salem and Fitzroy.

Bozz finds a spaceship made by his race, but Kruger finds them once more and tries to kill them. Bozz knocks the bomb into the ship and Kruger follows, only to be destroyed along with it.
name: Jan Kruger

deck: He is the son of Naruto Uzumaki, the Seventh Hokage, and Hinata Hyuuga. Brother to Himawari. He strongly dislikes the Hokage and seeks attention from his father. He is the grandson of the fourth hokage, Minato Namikaze.
description:
It's apparent that, because of Naruto Uzumaki's duty as the seventh hokage, he is receiving little attention from his father, and has pushed his feelings out in mischievous schemes, much like pre-shippuuden Naruto. It is currently unknown of what his goals are, if any, or any relationships he has with the other children in his academy. He does seem to have a friendly relationship with Shikadai Nara.

He is teammates with Sarada Uchiha and led by Konohamaru, and much to her chagrin, Boruto doesn't seem to care about the status of Hokage, or even the Chuunin Exams. He's quick to give up, as evident by his resolve to use cheap jutsu-creation mechanics, rather than hard work. He is currently looking to be trained under Sasuke Uchiha.
name: Boruto Uzumaki

deck: The daughter of Sakura Haruno and Sasuke Uchiha. She aspires to become Hokage when she's older.
description:
Overview

Sarada Uchiha is the daughter of Sasuke Uchiha and Sakura Haruno. She is a kunouchi of the Hidden Leaf Village, and is part of a ninja team along with Boruto Uzumaki, Mitsuki, and their sensei Konohamaru Sarutobi. When she was young, she had never seen her father and thus had a distant relationship with him. However, he has since made a better effort to be part of her life and the two have a better relationship now, spending time together when he returns to the village from his work. She has displayed interest in becoming Hokage and scolds Boruto every time he insults the title.

Story Arcs

Academy Days

During her days at the Academy, Sarada was one of the top students, keeping up the tradition that past Uchiha members had started. As the Academy Graduation exams drew near, Sarada went around Konoha with her friend Chocho Akimichi to pass the time. As Chocho complained about training with her dad, Sarada told her she should go through with it, not because she needed it, but because she should be glad that she has a father willing to spend time with her. As they run into Chocho's dad, Choji, Sarada makes her leave and runs into Boruto running away from his father after pulling a prank. After she helps him lose his father, Shikamaru Nara and his son show up on the scene and scold Boruto. All this only makes Sarada feel worse about not knowing her father, so she heads home to ask her mother about him. After Sakura gives her some unsavory answers, Sarada yells at her and causes her to punch the ground, sending their house crashing down. After Sakura is admitted to the hospital after feinting, Sarada returns to her home to recover any valuable items, and comes across her family portrait. Seeing the frame broken, Sarada picks up the picture and finds that the picture of her father is separate, and contains the picture of him and his old team, Team Hebi. Noticing that the girl in the picture has the same exact glasses that she does, Sarada comes to the conclusion that she is most likely her actual mother and not Sakura.

Search for her Father

Sarada then finds out that her birth isn't in any of the Konoha records, and becomes even angrier, choosing to leave the village and ask Sasuke himself who is her real mother. She heads over to the Hokage's office and overhears that Naruto Uzumaki (the Seventh Hokage) intends to meet up with Sasuke to discuss information he had gathered. She intends to follow the Hokage, but runs into Chocho, who for some reason also wants to find her real parents, because she believes she has other parents instead of the ones she has. As the two kunoichi are about to leave, they find Boruto with a bento lunch that he was supposed to give to his father, but he came too late. Sarada offers to take the lunch to him, and sets off with Chocho after Naruto.

Before they can reach them, however, they run into Shin Uchiha, a clone of his "father" Shin Uchiha of the same name, and are attacked. The two young girls put up a good fight, but Shin catches Chocho in a bad position and moves in to finish her. Luckily, Naruto comes onto the scene and intervenes, stopping the attack and saving the girl. After Shin leaves, the girls travel with Naruto for safety, and he tells Sarada stories about her father and his days when they were younger. Soon afterwards, the trio make there way to the tower where Naruto was supposed to meet with Sasuke, and an over eager Sarada rushes ahead to finally meet her dad. As she enters the building, however, Sasuke raises his sword at her, thinking she's friends with Shin who had also attacked Sasuke earlier.

After Sasuke recognizes her, Sarada gives him an earful for never being at home, not caring for her, and apparently lying about who her mother is. In a fit of rage, she storms out of the building to cool off, leaving Naruto, Sasuke, and Chocho behind. Outside, Naruto attempts to cheer her up, but before he can do that, the older Shin appears with about six smaller ones and attacks Sarada and Naruto. A fight ensues, and both Naruto and Sasuke are injured, which they chalk up to sloppy and rustiness. Before long, though, Sakura makes her way onto the scene and injures the older Shin so much so that he needs to retreat, but not before taking her with him. Sarada heads off with Naruto and Sasuke to one of Orochimaru's hideouts (now an ally of Konoha) to learn more about the Shin's that attacks them, and run into Suigetsu and Karin, the latter of whom she recognizes from the picture as her "would-be" mother. Pulling Suigetsu aside, Sarada asks him to run some tests to see whether or not Karin is actually her mother, and after testing an umbilical cord and a piece of Sarada's hair, the test comes back a perfect match, unknowing that the umbilical chord was actually Sakura's and not Karin's.

Sarada is brought to tears and shrugs off Naruto, calling him a liar and telling him she's going to leave Konoha and never return because the "family" she has right now isn't her related to her by blood. In response to this, Naruto tells her that it takes more than just blood to connect people in a family, and that all you need is love. As long as you care for your family, it doesn't matter if you're related by blood or not. Sarada eventually agrees and remembers the fond memories she has had with Sakura over the years. Now feeling better, she heads outside with Naruto and they travel with Sasuke to Shin's hideout.

Battle Against the Shins

Once there, they witness Shin attacking Sakura and another fight begins, this time with over a hundred little Shin clones. Naruto combats most of them with his Shadow Clones, but even more clones appear from behind the ninja. Wanting to show her mom how much she cares, Sarada charges forward and strikes the ground, displaying Sakura's immense strength and uttering her characteristic "Shanaro!" Just as this happens, Naruto manages to intimidate the Shin clones into submission, ending the fight prematurely. As Sarada embraces Sakura, she asks her "how can you be sure that your feelings are connected with my father's?" to which Sasuke replies, "Because we have you." Content with the family she has, Sarada and the group travel back home to Konoha and drop off the cloned Shin'a at an orphanage on the way. Once home, Sarada finally enjoys quality time with her dad until he has to leave. When she asks him when he'll be back, he gives her a hug and affectionately taps her forehead, just like his older brother used to do to him.

Chunin Exams

Some time later, Sarada and her team completed the needed number of missions to gain entrance to the Chunin Exam. Both her and Mitsuki were prepared to take the exam, but Sarada had to convince Boruto to take it, telling him that if he really wanted to defeat his father, he couldn't do so as a Genin. Sarada also dropped in from time to time on Boruto's lessons with her father, telling her dad to take it easy on him and to take his time during their lessons. As soon as Boruto signed his papers, the team was ready for the Chunin Exams. The first stage saw Sarada, her team, and the rest of the candidates outside and lined up before Proctors Shikamara and Sai and were asked an impossible, trick question about the fifth novel of a series that hasn't been written. After being asked to choose an answer, "True" or "False" and stand on the circle written on the ground, the Proctors pulled a lever and the two circles on the ground fell apart, dropping the candidates down two large holes towards a pit of black ink. Mitsuki saved the team with his special ability to stretch his limbs, and once they climbed out, Sarada learned that they had passed the first test by not allowing themselves to fall into the black ink. Excited, she took this news to her parents and awaited the next part of the Exam.

The second part of the exam took place in an abandoned, run down part of the village and consisted of capture the flag. Two teams were pitted against each other and tasked to either capture the other's flag or to knockout all the members of the opposing team. Sarada teamed up with Mitsuki to track down and locate the other team's flag, while Boruto stayed behind to guard their flag, with the help of his Shadow Clones. Sarada is thrown off by the fact that there are dozens of flag's on the enemy's roof, and deduces that it's a genjutsu set in place to fool her and Mitsuki while they try to take her flag. Using her Sharingan, Sarada breaks the illusion and locates the real flag, while at the same time Boruto defeated the team sent to take their flag, winning them the match.

In the final round of the Chunin Exams, contenders were put into one-on-one battles, just like the generation before them. Nearly the whole village was in attendance, as well as the other Kage from other villages. Sarada faces off against Tarui in her single match, and defeats her opponent by using her immense strength to send her opponent into the wall. Right after, Boruto is caught cheating in his match and disqualified, but as he has an argument with his father, Momoshiki and Kinshiki Ohtsutsuki appear and attack, kicking Naruto out of the stadium and nearly destroying it. Sarada helps Mitsuki to evacuate the bystanders, but as she's doing so a large piece of debris falls towards her. Before she realized it, Sasuke came and grabbed her away, taking her to the center of the stadium with Naruto and Boruto. As the two of them questioned the invaders, Sasuke revealed that they were the threat Kaguya was preparing for years ago, and soon Kinshiki set about destroying the stadium completely. Using his Nine Tails powers, Naruto manages to protect the three of them and save the village from being destroyed by Kinshiki's Tailed Beast Ball-like jutsu, but was kidnapped after he passed out. Sarada informed Boruto of this after he woke, and then later wished him luck as he traveled with the other Kage and Sasuke into a different dimension to retrieve Naruto.

After the team returned with Naruto and news that they had defeated the new villains, business went back to usual for Sarada and her team. Sitting atop the Hokage Monument, Sarada and Mitsuki congratulate Boruto on his recent accomplishments, chide him for cheating during the exam, and again ask him if he's going to try to become Hokage like his father and grandfather before him. He tells her that he wants to write his own story and make his own path, like her father did, and offers to become Sarada's aide when she becomes Hokage. She agrees, and her team jumps off to capture an escaped bear as part of their new mission.
